A houseslave came in, announcing the arrival of her guest. A glass of Neriak Nectar was poured just as her Unseen Blade entered. &quot;Good day to you, (name deleted just to tick you all off)&quot;, Morrigu said. &quot;Will you sup with me?&quot;. She and her visitor moved to the table and sat, not at opposite ends as protocol would dictate, but at adjacent corners like old friends. Houselaves continuously brough such delicacies as pate of Feir'Dal liver, Gnome finger sandwiches and Morrigu's favorite (but quite gouche) dish of Pickled Halfling toes. <br>
They talked long into the night, discussing events of Norrath, the state of the Teir'Dal nation, and other things. Morrigu told her Hidden Blade of the two cousins she had recently ordered the City Council of Neriak to appoint to the ranks of the city guards. The even discussed the salary to be paid as a head of Morrigu's inner staff. <br>
Toward the dawn, Morrigu bid her lieutenant a fond farewell and retired for some much-needed sleep. Her recent efforts on several fronts had worn her out. <br>
Unable to sleep, she lay tossing on magnificent spider-silk sheets on her huge bed in the Matron's chambers. Morrigu reflected on her life, and found that she was not at all where she had planned. Always shying away from politics and power as a child, she had preferred to sport with other children at games of strength and skill. She had even relished her studies in her early childhood at the Wizard's academy, where all the elders assured her parents that she would meet or exceed their legacy to the arts. But this life was so....not at all what she had forseen. She longed for the days following her abandonment of her family, where she had made her way as a poor street-urchin working for the Ebon Mask. She had felt so at home there. And later, when she had been accepted into the House D'Fral, the Obsidian Blade, she had known kinship like never before. But many of those were gone now, and she had had to step up to sit on the Blade's council. <br>
She spared a few moments on all of this, and then her thoughts drifted to her mrann d'ssinss, Kaelin. Word had reached her that he was in a far-off land, and not at all well. Perhaps she would have to put everything here away for awhile, and do something about that...Perhaps... <br>
Morrigu drifted of finally to blissful slumber <br>
