In a long string of sparring matches, she had been bested by only two opponents; Her brother Kiros, and Dantrazz W'Rath. The battle with Kiros had been closer, and has she been using poisoned blades it would have been decidedly in her favor. The battle with Dantrazz had been different. Only once before has she fought so hard to win a battle. As she saw herself slowly losing to Dan's mighty blows, she felt something inside of her yielding to him. She fought no less valiantly, in fact she frantically scrabbled to turn the tide of the conflict. But something inside of her was releasing itself to this man, who drew her attention and intrest. <br>
<br>
Later, during the Council meeting, she had excused herself to fetch a gift for the newest rogue in the house Javaan, the house of the snake. Isildark had been promised a guilding gift from the leader of his house, and with her absence she had neglected him. Making her way back to the council meeting, she had been tasked by Kiros to invite Brenya to join the Obsidian Blade. Her heart had frozen at the name, but she conducted her duty, and welcomed Brenya with open arms, heart breaking the entire time. <br>
<br>
After the battle for Dantrazz' freedom, she had been in a state of shock. She knew he had fought for himself, and had not chosen her over Brenya. But something inside of her rejoiced at his strength, his nobility. If any among the Teir'Dal deserved to live free, it was Dantrazz W'Rath. They had talked long into the night, and she had enjoyed his company. His kiss had taken her by surprise, but was by no means unwelcome. <br>
<br>
As she finished her duties in the household of F'Lok and began to prepare to retire for the evening, her thoughts drifted to him. He was so...perfect for her in every way. Too many coincidences. The assassin and politician in her reared their heads and screamed that she was being drawn into a trap. There were to many coincidences, the timing was too perfect. They had a common enemy in Lokus, they both loved to wander the region of lake Rathetear and admire the beauty there, they both had debts to pay in blood...and they both recognized a sickness within the Teir'Dal society. Was she paranoid enough to believe she was being set up to take a tremendous fall? Or was there something else to this, something even more important than her wealth and status within the city? Something without which life of any kind had no purpose... <br>
<br>
She quickly put such thoughts out of her head. If this be a trap, she would walk into it with open arms. Jala cahallin xal tlu elg'cahlin (any food may be poison) had been a principle she had lived by for too long. A life in fear of shadows was no life at all. <br>
<br>
And so, in her release from the worries of status, wealth and life, Morrigu also had found her freedom. What will be, will be. <br>
